anvil.api.Command

Interface CommandExecutionData


  • public interface CommandExecutionData
    Represents the Execution data for a CommandType. This is where the actual execution of a Command can be specified.

    The execution of a Command should be considered event-based, meaning that it should either be entirely self-contained, or take into account all possible constraints necessary for functionality.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Garrett Stonis
    See Also:
    CommandType, CommandResult

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        <T extends CommandResult> T execute(java.lang.String[] args)
        This is run by the wrapper's Command parser when the command is called. Should be considered event-based, meaning that it should either entirely self-contained, or take into account all possible constraints necessary for functionality.

        If an exception is thrown by any part of this method, it will be caught, and a Failed object (with the message "The Command threw a(n) [Exception name]!") is returned. This will be given to Anvil to process and to the caller of the command.

        Type Parameters:
        T - Any class that extends the CommandResult class.
        Parameters:
        args - String array containing the arguments for the command instance.
        Returns:
        Object extending CommandResult representing the success of the Command.
